Söngvakeppni Sjónvarpsins 2007 was the show in which Iceland selected its entry for the Eurovision Song Contest 2007, held in Helsinki, Finland.
The winner was Eiríkur Hauksson with the song "Ég Les Í Lófa Þínum".
Hauksson had represented Iceland at the Eurovision Song Contest 1986, as a member of the band ICY.
